[{"id":30602,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Hydrocarbons","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></mfenced><mo>&#60;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi></mfenced><mo>&#60;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></mfenced><mo>&#60;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></mfenced><mo>&#60;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi></mfenced><mo>&#60;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi></mfenced><mo>&#60;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi></mfenced><mo>&#60;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></mfenced><mo>&#60;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi></mfenced><mo>&#60;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi></mfenced><mo>&#60;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></mfenced><mo>&#60;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></mfenced><mo>&#60;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi></mfenced></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8211;</mo><msub><mi>OCH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi></math> effect so, ring activating group and ortho para directing.<br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8211;</mo><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mo>+</mo></math> hyperconjugation &amp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></math> so, ring activating group (ortho para directing).<br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8211;</mo><mi>NH</mi><mn>2</mn><mo>=</mo></math>&nbsp;Here the aniline is the least reactive due to formation of anilinium ion in acidic medium. It will now act as strong <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></math> group.<br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8211;</mo><mi>Cl</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>&#8211;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi></math> so, ring deactivating &amp; meta directing.&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2018 (15 Apr)","image":null},{"id":30604,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Hydrocarbons","question":"","options":["<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/123nvbdjbv.PNG\" style=\"width: 75px; height: 86px;\" />","<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/2dnvkdvvs.PNG\" style=\"width: 105px; height: 90px;\" />","<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/3n3jr.PNG\" style=\"width: 62px; height: 116px;\" />","<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/4dnkdnk.PNG\" style=\"width: 79px; height: 111px;\" />"],"answer":0,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/vgkjekexakqdfgoxpwierocbtibkmwrsimlcspdfhkbacjenhd.jpeg\" /><br /><br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/jygyjcnbdxavorhzvsddbjepsamormwbalevqmwbqlgjdgrsfr.jpeg\" /><br /><br /><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/DEVA12.jpeg\" style=\"width: 260px; height: 130px;\" />","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2017 (09 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":30421,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Hydrocarbons","question":"","options":["2","0","1","4"],"answer":1,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/yW3Ys9uSKQM9Bs55QFy8HgybxiI4Y9lwiAFNI2aIpiU.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (7 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":30508,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Hydrocarbons","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/bc4a928b-bded-4b61-bf82-d7b41554a127-image.png\" style=\"width: 100px; height: 149px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/3af17e56-2eab-4d1f-91b0-c25a45430c17-image.png\" style=\"width: 100px; height: 163px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/28946a68-8461-4076-abda-b712eaf29eb1-image.png\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 180px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/13fa77d1-d395-4597-913c-18813b769e25-image.png\" style=\"width: 90px; height: 160px;\" />"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>In the first step ethyl benzene undergoes electrophilic substitution reaction to form&nbsp;1-Bromo-4-ethylbenzene.</p><p>In the next&nbsp;step&nbsp;1-Bromo-4-ethylbenzene undergoes free radical substitution at benzylic position followed by dehydrohalogenation(last step) in presence of alcoholic KOH to form 4-bromo styrene.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/d21191c7-7593-49f2-8a81-7c48c7ad3639-Untitled.png\" style=\"width: 430px; height: 510px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (27 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":30416,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Hydrocarbons","question":"","options":["5-methylhex-2-yne","Isopropylbut-1-yne","2-methylhex-3-yne","2-methylhex-2-yne"],"answer":2,"solution":"<br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (22 January Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":30549,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Hydrocarbons","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mo>&#8594;</mo><mrow><mi>Sn</mi><mo>/</mo><mi>HCl</mi></mrow></mover><mo>/</mo><mover><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>KBr</mi></mover><mo>/</mo><mover><mo>&#8594;</mo><msub><mi>Br</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mover><mo>/</mo><mover><mo>&#8594;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></mover></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mo>&#8594;</mo><mrow><msub><mi>Br</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>/</mo><mi>Fe</mi></mrow></mover><mo>/</mo><mover><mo>&#8594;</mo><mrow><mi>Sn</mi><mo>/</mo><mi>HCl</mi></mrow></mover><mo>/</mo><mover><mo>&#8594;</mo><mrow><msub><mi>NaNO</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>/</mo><mi>HCl</mi></mrow></mover><mo>/</mo><mover><mo>&#8594;</mo><mrow><mi>CuBr</mi><mo>/</mo><mi>HBr</mi></mrow></mover></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mo>&#8594;</mo><msub><mi>NaNO</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mover><mo>/</mo><mover><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>HCl</mi></mover><mo>/</mo><mover><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>KBr</mi></mover><mo>/</mo><mover><mo>&#8594;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></mover></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mo>&#8594;</mo><mrow><mi>Sn</mi><mo>/</mo><mi>HCl</mi></mrow></mover><mo>/</mo><mover><mo>&#8594;</mo><msub><mi>Br</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mover><mo>/</mo><mover><mo>&#8594;</mo><msub><mi>NaNO</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mover><mo>/</mo><mover><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>NaBr</mi></mover></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>The process of conversion of primary aromatic amines into its&nbsp;diazonium&nbsp;salt is called&nbsp;diazotization.&nbsp;</p><p>Diazonium&nbsp;salts are important synthetic intermediates that can undergo coupling&nbsp;reactions&nbsp;to form azo dyes and electrophilic substitution&nbsp;reactions&nbsp;to introduce functional groups.</p><p>The&nbsp;correct sequence of reagents used for converting nitrobenzene into m- dibromobenzene is found in option (b).</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/aefa6f34-12ff-4a77-af80-87730cc54f35-image.png\" style=\"width: 373px; height: 353px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (24 Feb Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":30630,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Hydrocarbons","question":"","options":["benzoyl chloride","benzyl chloride","$o-$and $p-$chlorotoluene","$m-$chlorotoluene"],"answer":2,"solution":"Due to $\\mathrm{o}$ - and $\\mathrm{p}$ - directing nature of $\\mathrm{CH}_3$ group.\n<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/Z2QFHkPMBT3TAto6UyUX6bERW2KKKhUghc367d1S9VU.original.fullsize.png\"><br>\nHence, (C) is correct answer.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2007","image":null},{"id":30494,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Hydrocarbons","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/e906fac1-6bcd-4b2d-854c-aeee0cde8e2b-image.png\" style=\"width: 256px; height: 100px;\" />","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/81b86a68-fb30-4e0d-a356-74a2669291e7-image.png\" style=\"width: 188px; height: 120px;\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/99e0b3bd-22cc-425d-b8ba-3d538d7ed31d-image.png\" style=\"width: 278px; height: 100px;\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/868e1e10-2043-4882-9f83-7652cf45b8de-image.png\" style=\"width: 232px; height: 100px;\" /></p>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Ozone is a very reactive allotrope of oxygen. The reaction of ozone with alkenes and alkynes causes the oxidative cleaving of the alkene or alkyne. The carbon-carbon double bonds are replaced with carbon-oxygen double bonds, giving the required carbonyl product as shown below.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/e77ae704-4bcf-420c-a398-3f57ef5a9af5-6a3d76ae-7a7f-46e0-a6de-46c9c658d93c-image.png\" style=\"width: 420px; height: 217px;\" /></p><p>In all other options both compounds will give the same product on ozonolysis.</p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (29 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":30613,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Hydrocarbons","question":"","options":["Cat. Hydrogenation","$\\mathrm{H}_2$ /Lindlar Cat.","$\\mathrm{Li} / \\mathrm{NH}_3$","$\\mathrm{LiAlH}_4$"],"answer":2,"solution":"With Lithium in liquid ammonia, trans-alkene is almost an exclusive product.\n<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/iILAqqxgUCghpdRGQXl9Fpu8xzOsO-DaL7FUQEjSS_Q.original.fullsize.png\"><br><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/FZ2MuL0spbt_NnchNabKz1XgCdRXyo1-anxAfuCxZB8.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2014 (11 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":30517,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Hydrocarbons","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CI</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mi>COOK</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>HCOOK</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CI</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mi>COOK</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>HCOOH</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CHI</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mi>COOK</mi></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mi>CH</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mover><mo>&#10230;</mo><mrow><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>+</mo></msup><mo>/</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></mrow></mover><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msub><mi>CHOHCH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mfrac><mi>KIO</mi><mrow><mi>dil</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>KOH</mi></mrow></mfrac><msub><mi>CHI</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mi>COOK</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (01 Sep Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":30567,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Hydrocarbons","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/c7b8056c-9e29-4d01-80dd-6a44aadded77.png\" style=\"height: 51px; width: 180px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/65dc09c3-1076-4189-beba-a03d11511b05.png\" style=\"height: 93px; width: 150px;\" />","<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mover><mrow><mo>→</mo></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">r</mi></mrow></mover></math>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/3441151d-5dd9-40bd-b94a-3d23d707d22c.png\" style=\"height: 76px; width: 200px;\" />"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>A solution of two enantiomers that are present in an equal ratio is known as the racemic mixture. Here the reaction sequence is given below. It is clearly seen from the final product that it is not the racemic&nbsp;product because it does not have any chiral&nbsp;carbon.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/66e2530e-3b31-484a-b8f9-eb55412b0a99-image.png\" style=\"width: 400px; height: 337px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (09 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":30445,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Hydrocarbons","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/9K08PirQy1-FZ_BdMyhi9w08lQermKOOm0V73RVFrcw.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","A - \\(\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{CH}_3 \\quad \\mathrm{~B}-\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{CH}_3\\)","\\(\\mathrm{A}-\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{CH}_2-\\mathrm{OH} \\quad \\mathrm{B}-\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{CH}_2-\\mathrm{OH}\\)","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/heFvwCDqjihq67pmXnXF9GfDz5mpxqGSd6FLYFvAOX0.original.fullsize.png\"><br>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/dtwULf_g6PlHkJDSBLKBioOqr_VDiCeVWEac6nqDmeE.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (09 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":30474,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Hydrocarbons","question":"","options":["Butanal and acetaldehyde","Butanoic acid and acetaldehyde","Butanal and acetic acid","Butanoic acid and acetic acid"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>Ozone will cleave carbon-carbon double bonds to give ketones/carboxylic acids after oxidative workup. Here in this reaction Cleavage occurs at unsaturation of hexene and Butanoic acid and acetic acid is formed.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/c8c23681-181c-4be7-821e-7e37c6776aeb.png\" style=\"width: 465px; height: 84px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (12 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":30608,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Hydrocarbons","question":"","options":["Isobutane","Ethane","Butane","Propane"],"answer":3,"solution":"Combustion of Hydrocarbon,<br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">y</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">y</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><msub><mi>CO</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">y</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>&#8733;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">v</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mo>)</mo></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>for</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mn>1</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi>mole</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi>of</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi>CxHy</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">y</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>required</mi></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>for</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mn>5</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi>of</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi>CxHy</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">y</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>required</mi></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>ratio</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi>of</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi>alkane</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>and</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi>is</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mn>5</mn><mo>/</mo><mn>25</mn></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>So</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">y</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mn>5</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>25</mn></math><br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">y</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn></math>,<br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>which</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi>is</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi>satisfied</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi>by</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>8</mn></msub></math>.<br />&nbsp;","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2016 (09 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":30504,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Hydrocarbons","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>The Alkanes and their mono bromo dervative are as given below,</p><p>There are three alkanes possible with the formula<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mn>5</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>12</mn></msub></math>,</p><p>n-pentane, iso-pentane and neo-pentane.</p><p>And identify the possible mono bromo derivatives formed by each isomer.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/da9ffa52-6ca6-4163-b8c0-bdd102df3d10-image.png\" style=\"width: 524px; height: 280px;\" />​​​​​​​</p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (25 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":30450,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Hydrocarbons","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/JBOQzqgRI7DMT2utn-ZSD6zZsmcoLVGj4Kj2zaG0Bqk.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/CJQzR1UQ26sY0P3vYtG2Kf0TBarcu9ExCM1zs213H60.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/s6wGZboOxO6ToeBGJK07golMw6EZIYMh6lNvVvyBaOs.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/lgt-Q-IaWk4z316g7xMqFOAQO96CORulSjXcaxJKAIs.original.fullsize.png\"><br>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/faVl-R3_ZyU0rIbCXNrXh-wSXj9RqbRb44fi41Di6NM.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (04 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":30571,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Hydrocarbons","question":"","options":["<math><msub><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>a</mi></mrow></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>c</mi></mrow></msub></math>","<math><msub><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>a</mi></mrow></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>c</mi></mrow></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub></math>","<math><msub><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>c</mi></mrow></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>a</mi></mrow></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub></math>","<math><msub><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>c</mi></mrow></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>a</mi></mrow></msub></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>logk</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>logA</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></msub><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>.303</mo><mi>RT</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p>Slope <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></msub><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>.303</mo><mi>RT</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>&#10233;</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi></msub><mo>&#62;</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></msub><mo>&#62;</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></msub><mo>&#62;</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi></msub></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (08 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":30479,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Hydrocarbons","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>When 2-methyl butene-2 is subjected to ozonolysis and then reduced in presence of dimethyl sulphide or Zn dust, it yields acetone and acetaldehyde. Cycloaddition of a molecule of ozone occurs first and then it is cleaved reductively to give aldehyde and ketone.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/0fff387a-ae61-40b9-8aa1-51df6c21d667.png\" style=\"width: 500px; height: 140px;\" /></p><p>&nbsp;</p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (08 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":30611,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Hydrocarbons","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/aozm_O6UvGkOjaLnTBdcvHVDdj5reVZXRANFHkQl75g.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/dEAcUA_bWi_nWVNOlJlLrAUVNR-dG63On8DjQLrDWXs.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/_-jl5HFr4gUgYvfUK8fTPKGHvJLaDm1U1umq6ND00YM.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/JiDpHC_O8yqrCvHIIlgtCIGuEl7d87HbjLdv46-fTJs.original.fullsize.png\"><br>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/rXjNhFEyXOiYoKEJOtZ9Gp8RkiMUepMb4j2VW0EZZCc.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2014 (12 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":30402,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Hydrocarbons","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"Step 1: The first reaction is a Friedel-Crafts alkylation. Benzene reacts with $CH_3Cl$ in the presence of anhydrous $AlCl_3$ to form toluene.<br><br>Step 2: The second reaction is electrophilic aromatic substitution. Toluene reacts with $Cl_2$ in the presence of $FeCl_3$ to form a mixture of o-chlorotoluene and p-chlorotoluene. Due to steric hindrance at the ortho position, the major product is p-chlorotoluene.<br><br>Step 3: The third reaction is the oxidation of the alkyl side chain. p-chlorotoluene is oxidized by $K_2Cr_2O_7 / H_2SO_4$ to form p-chlorobenzoic acid, which is the major product $(X)$.<br><br>The molecular formula of p-chlorobenzoic acid is $C_7H_5ClO_2$.<br>Molar mass of $(X) = (7 \\times 12) + (5 \\times 1) + 35.5 + (2 \\times 16) = 84 + 5 + 35.5 + 32 = 156.5 \\text{ g mol}^{-1}$.<br><br>Step 4: Reaction of p-chlorobenzoic acid with $NaHCO_3$ liberates $CO_2$ gas:<br>$C_6H_4ClCOOH + NaHCO_3 \\rightarrow C_6H_4ClCOONa + H_2O + CO_2 \\uparrow$<br><br>From the stoichiometry, $1$ mole of p-chlorobenzoic acid produces $1$ mole of $CO_2$ gas.<br>Volume of $CO_2$ liberated at STP = $11.2 \\text{ dm}^3$.<br>Moles of $CO_2$ liberated = $\\dfrac{11.2}{22.4} = 0.5 \\text{ mol}$.<br><br>Therefore, moles of p-chlorobenzoic acid reacted = $0.5 \\text{ mol}$.<br>Mass of $(X)$ reacted, $P = 0.5 \\text{ mol} \\times 156.5 \\text{ g mol}^{-1} = 78.25 \\text{ g}$.<br><br>Answer: $78.25$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (04 April Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":30410,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Hydrocarbons","question":"","options":["steam distillation","simple distillation","sublimation","fractional distillation"],"answer":3,"solution":"Benzene reacts with $\\text{Br}_2$ in the presence of $\\text{FeBr}_3$ (Friedel-Crafts halogenation) to give bromobenzene.<br><br>Bromobenzene on nitration with $\\text{HNO}_3 / \\text{H}_2\\text{SO}_4$ gives a mixture of ortho-bromonitrobenzene and para-bromonitrobenzene (since $-\\text{Br}$ is an ortho/para director).<br><br>The two products (B and C) are separated by fractional distillation method due to their different boiling points.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (28 January Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":30470,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Hydrocarbons","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Ph</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/a28b0498-b247-4c00-9edb-a1244c57ce59.png\" style=\"width: 290px; height: 155px;\"/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/5f6ed249-ffe6-4519-b2a0-2776777b595d.png\" style=\"width: 290px; height: 154px;\"/>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Ph</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><mi>OH</mi></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>The Hydroboration Oxidation reaction is an organic chemical reaction which is employed for the conversion of alkenes into alcohols that are neutral.</p><p>The hydroboration oxidation reaction mechanism can be considered as an anti-markownikov's reaction where a hydroxyl group attaches itself to the carbon which is less substituted. </p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/d1243050-516e-499d-aea4-1d112e3ec222.png\" style=\"width: 500px; height: 194px;\"/></p><p>Hence, the answer is option D.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (27 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":30429,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Hydrocarbons","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/iD-rDE4lVnB5OY5A7RuMNKyqOo1CTK7lPuIaSQ-pgC8.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/RLI8jwTeARTrwXMqSi1szyiiR-gkUD7Z7GeFwd7WULI.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/G2nevmJ1Yo4lieBOt1nbpHn0S_uJeyOFyVxe__xk7m8.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/_WIAscbFHK2KuxjIOG1lM8N2wNU-fFXZkz_BVpoPgnQ.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/Z_tHnygHAa8TD6ZtSBz5TihmaICZFE3vIkNHqA5bUV0.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (3 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":30432,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Hydrocarbons","question":"","options":["Both Statement I and Statement II are false","Statement I is false but Statement II is true","Statement I is true but Statement II is false","Both Statement I and Statement II are true"],"answer":3,"solution":"Statement - I\n<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/7DOskX3KltiHBjhdCMXygh84hmFOYqm1Xu7mn20mGBs.original.fullsize.png\"><br>\n\nStatement-II $-\\mathrm{CH}_3$ group is o/p directing while $-\\mathrm{NO}_2$ group is meta directing.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (29 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":30482,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Hydrocarbons","question":"","options":["B and C only","B, C and D only","A, C and D only","A and B only"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>A: Cis - But-2-ene</p><p>B: Trans - But-2-ene</p><p>More polar molecules are more soluble in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></math>. Hence A &gt;B.</p><p>Molecules having higher dipole moments have higher boiling points due to larger intermolecular&nbsp;forces of attraction.&nbsp;More symmetric isomers have higher melting points due to better packing in crystalline lattice &amp; trans isomers are more symmetric than cis. Hence, in case of boiling point it is A&gt;B and in case of melting point it is B&gt;A.</p><p>cis-isomer has resultant of dipoles while in trans isomer dipole moments cancel out.&nbsp;</p><p>So, the correct answer is B, C and D only.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (01 Feb Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":30465,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Hydrocarbons","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>During ozonolysis, O<sub>3</sub>​ adds across C=C, and it produces ozonide.</p><p>The ozonide on hydrolysis produces carbonyl compounds. The reaction is used to locate double bond in alkene.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/0b59cbff-8372-4716-90b8-689b175de2f9.png\" style=\"width: 600px; height: 122px;\"/></p><p>Hence total number of oxygen atom present per molecule of <img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/7d97bfff-6614-4987-975d-65bb857e3e99.png\" style=\"width: 150px; height: 89px;\"/></p><p> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math>.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (29 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":30426,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Hydrocarbons","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/hHNWVjTmd6n6Sx-KkIKtkVZApwAbJcJ58pIDwQGS0z0.original.fullsize.png\"/><br />$\\begin{array}{ll}\\mathrm{C}_6 \\mathrm{H}_5 \\mathrm{NO}_2 & \\mathrm{MF}=\\mathrm{C}_6 \\mathrm{H}_4 \\mathrm{~N}_2 \\mathrm{O}_4 \\\\ \\mathrm{MW}=123 & \\mathrm{MW}=168 \\\\ & \\therefore \\frac{4.2}{168}=0.025 \\mathrm{~mol}\\end{array}$<br />$\\because$ required gm of nitro benzene<br />$\\begin{aligned}<br />& =123 \\times 0.025 \\\\<br>& =3.075<br />\\end{aligned}$<br />$\\therefore$ Nearest integer is 3","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (3 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":30500,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Hydrocarbons","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>6</mn></msub></math> and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>Cl</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>&#729;</mo></mover><msub><mi>HCl</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math> and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>&#729;</mo></mover></math> and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>HCl</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>6</mn></msub></math> and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>HCl</mi></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<blockquote><p>In summer season, chlorine atoms&nbsp;forming chlorine sinks, preventing much ozone depletion, whereas In winter, special type of clouds called polar stratospheric clouds are formed over Antarctica.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>&#8226;</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mfenced><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mfenced><mo>&#8594;</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>&#8226;</mo></mover><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>HCl</mi><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mfenced></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (26 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":30413,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Hydrocarbons","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"Benzene reacts with $\\text{CH}_3\\text{-CO-CH}_2\\text{-CH}_2\\text{-CO-Cl}$ in the presence of anhydrous $\\text{AlCl}_3$ (Friedel-Crafts acylation) to give product P (a keto-ketone).<br>P on treatment with aq. NaOH and heating undergoes intramolecular aldol condensation to give a cyclic enone Q.<br>Molecular mass of Q $= 157$<br>Percentage of oxygen in Q $= \\frac{16}{157} \\times 100 = 10.19\\% \\approx 10\\%$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (23 January Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":30615,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Hydrocarbons","question":"","options":["Acetylene","Ethene","2 - Butyne","2 - Butene"],"answer":2,"solution":"The 1, 1, 1 - trichloroethane&nbsp;form ​&nbsp;2-butyne&nbsp;when reacted with silver powder.<br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msub><mi>CCl</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>Ag</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#8594;</mo><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>&#8801;</mo><msub><mi>CCH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>AgCl</mi></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2014 (06 Apr)","image":null},{"id":30393,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Hydrocarbons","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"The general formula of an alkane is $C_n H_{2n+2}$.<br><br>The balanced chemical equation for the complete combustion of an alkane is:<br><br>$C_n H_{2n+2} + \\left(\\dfrac{3n+1}{2}\\right) O_2 \\rightarrow n CO_2 + (n+1) H_2O$<br><br>Given that $8$ moles of oxygen are required for complete combustion:<br><br>$\\dfrac{3n+1}{2} = 8$<br><br>$3n + 1 = 16$<br><br>$n = 5$<br><br>The molecular formula of the alkane $(Y)$ is $C_5H_{12}$.<br><br>Since $(Y)$ yields only one monochlorinated product $(Z)$ upon reaction with $Cl_2/h\\nu$, all the hydrogen atoms in the alkane must be equivalent.<br><br>Among the isomers of $C_5H_{12}$ (n-pentane, isopentane, and neopentane), only 2,2-dimethylpropane (neopentane) has all equivalent hydrogen atoms.<br><br>The structure of neopentane is $C(CH_3)_4$.<br><br>In this structure, the central carbon is quaternary, and the four surrounding methyl carbons are primary carbon atoms.<br><br>Therefore, the total number of primary carbon atoms in $(Y)$ is $4$.<br><br>Answer: $4$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (06 April Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":30523,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Hydrocarbons","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/4f7eb4e3-783f-4b49-852b-1303f6beb194-image.png\" style=\"width: 210px; height: 84px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/d74566dc-6bd0-458e-9474-1bf01861343c-image.png\" style=\"width: 210px; height: 84px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/aaf1838e-53b5-4c99-9ce7-d162438cabf7-image.png\" style=\"width: 220px; height: 124px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/2cf5c8c2-0e0f-4cdc-89e0-01d9fddb70ad-image.png\" style=\"width: 158px; height: 124px;\" />"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>This reaction follows the free radical mechanism as follows:</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/8a6e4570-9e23-4b93-b5b2-73e781c9bc4f-image.png\" style=\"width: 464px; height: 112px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (26 Aug Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":30566,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Hydrocarbons","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/45aa295f-cb49-4a18-8fb2-a9ee2dfbd583-image.png\" style=\"width: 144px; height: 76px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/c012048c-fdb8-4e6c-bf96-c8f57e28da6f-image.png\" style=\"width: 118px; height: 94px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/b0662f0e-a260-4d27-aa61-85c7fd848c96-image.png\" style=\"width: 115px; height: 109px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/4c1389e8-f756-4db2-a69c-aa5ff07f29ac-image.png\" style=\"width: 133px; height: 120px;\" />"],"answer":1,"solution":"&nbsp;","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (02 Sep Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":30584,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Hydrocarbons","question":"","options":["<math><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></math>","<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></math>","<math><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></math>","<math><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">F</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>Markovnikov&rsquo;s product is formed when a stable carbocation is formed on the more substituted carbon.</p><p>In <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">F</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>,</mo></math> the carbocation formed will be destabilized by strong <math><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></math> group of <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">F</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub><mo>.</mo></math> Hence, the Anti-Markovnikov&rsquo;s product will be formed.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/188a3e1f-5572-4059-81a2-08fabeb9dd35-image.png\" style=\"width: 684px; height: 117px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (08 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":30558,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Hydrocarbons","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/db713a3b-7fa6-499e-b49e-9a9729cf67d2-image.png\" style=\"width: 150px; height: 155px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/744cff1c-cd4b-45cb-8067-285045cd15b7-image.png\" style=\"width: 150px; height: 158px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/49bd390a-29e1-4a36-88b7-a3a3ba809d8e-image.png\" style=\"width: 120px; height: 157px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/59f514d2-9056-43f6-9b77-0e6b57c52a84-image.png\" style=\"width: 120px; height: 184px;\" />"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/424f104b-4dbc-4fe3-a6fd-4721d8610bfb-image.png\" style=\"width: 575px; height: 146px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (05 Sep Shift 2)","image":null}]